'From Squeak2.8alpha of 4 February 2000 [latest update: #2310] on 12 June 2000 at 12:59:43 pm'!"Change Set:		129SysWinVisible-mirDate:			31 May 2000Author:			Michael RuegerThis change set works around a bug in SystemWindow causing windows to be repositioned on a Squeak (native) window collapse and restore."!!SystemWindow methodsFor: 'drawing' stamp: 'mir 5/30/2000 17:20'!makeMeVisible 	self world extent > (0@0) ifFalse: [^ self].	((self world bounds insetBy: (0@0 corner: self labelHeight asPoint))		containsPoint: self position) ifTrue: [^ self "OK -- at least my top left is visible"].	"window not on screen (probably due to reframe) -- move it now"	self isCollapsed		ifTrue: [self position: (RealEstateAgent assignCollapsePointFor: self)]		ifFalse: [self position: (RealEstateAgent initialFrameFor: self initialExtent: self extent) topLeft].! !